Right, to get a different disk icon to appear when you insert a 'bad' disk
into the drive...  (Well it`s nice when I`m using PC0: and DF0: is of course
not recognised)

1) Load icon edit
2) Design your disk... (Or adapt the default one - select type to disk
                        and hit new)
3) Save your disk as default
4) Go to shell
5) type:         cd envarc:sys
6) type:         copy def_disk.info def_kick.info
7) load your favourite binary file editor...
   for me:    zap def_kick.info
8) Change offset $30 to 7  (It is currently 1)
9) Reboot and insert a 'duff' disk and watch the correct icon appear.

Hope this solves the problems....

Justin.


