In a message of 17 Apr 94 Mike Austin wrote about Hide a device icon?:

 MA> Plainly put, is there any way to hide a device's icon on the Workbench?

 MA> I want to set up a Temp: partition, but I don't want that on my
 MA> Workbench. Thanks...

All you have to do is to put an 'Assign Temp: DISMOUNT' in your User-Startup.
If you still want to refer to the partition as Temp:, you have to assign it to
the device name after the dismount. If the device name of your Temp: partition
were DH2:, it would look like this in your User-Startup:

...
Assign Temp: DISMOUNT
Assign Temp: DH2:
...

