O, MY GAWD !  It can't be Matthias Fleischer, who writes to All ?! And it's
about Mounting second ram: drive too !


 MF> Subject says it all:
 MF> Is it possible to mount a second ram: drive ? (not the fixed-sized rad:,
 MF> but the one that is mounted
 MF>  automatically at system startup)

 MF> I tried a mountlist entry with
 MF> filesystem = ram  (This is the name of the handler AFAIK) stack = 4096
 MF> globvec = 0 (tried out -1, too)

Almost right.  Try :

    Handler=ram-handler
    Stack=4096
    GlobVec=0

That should do it.  It's been awhile since I did this myself (way back in the
good old KS1.3 days), but I remember you had to relabel the new drive before
you loaded Workbench.  There will be conflicts otherwise. So, assuming your
second RAM drive is called RAM1:, use :

; setting up the new ramdrive
Mount RAM1:
Relabel RAM1: "Second RAM drive"


G'bye then,

